I am applying because:

* I'd like to work on widely on ubuntu packages set
* I'd like to eliminate delays in getting my work sponsored.
* I'd like to reduce the burden on my sponsors.

== Who I am ==

I'm an ubuntu-desktop developer and debian maintainer for the whole gnome-team mset and some other freedesktop packages, I've been involved both upstream and downstream in the GNOME project for many years and I work on everything that can be related to the best desktop experience, including system daemons or low level libraries.

== My Ubuntu story ==

I'm using ubuntu since 5.04, and started building packages for it quite early on (starting with compiz project).

I've joined the ubuntu-desktop team on 2020, after various years of sponsored work.

Since then I've various of uploads in both the desktop and other package sets.

=== My involvement ===
=== Examples of my work / Things I'm proud of ===

* merges/syncs: many, see below 
* Contributed to getting newest GNOME in many ubuntu versions
* SRUs: I care about keeping stable releases both updated, fixed and stable so I spend quite some time in stable backports

<pre>
SELECT source, version, date, changed_by, changed_by_name,
       changed_by_email, signed_by, signed_by_name, signed_by_email,
       distribution,
       array_to_string(ARRAY(
         SELECT bug
         FROM ubuntu_upload_history_launchpad_closes
         WHERE source = ubuntu_upload_history.source
           AND version = ubuntu_upload_history.version
       ), ' ') AS fixed
FROM ubuntu_upload_history
WHERE lower(signed_by) LIKE lower('%Marco Trevisan%')
ORDER BY date DESC

Via `udd` query:

<pre>
WITH debian_source AS (
    SELECT source, version, signed_by
    FROM upload_history
)
SELECT u.source, u.version, u.date, u.changed_by, u.changed_by_name,
       u.changed_by_email, u.signed_by, u.signed_by_name, u.signed_by_email,
       u.distribution, d.signed_by AS signed_by_debian, 
      array_to_string(ARRAY(
                 SELECT bug
                 FROM ubuntu_upload_history_launchpad_closes
                 WHERE source = u.source
                   AND version = u.version
               ), ' ') AS fixed
FROM ubuntu_upload_history u
LEFT JOIN debian_source d ON d.source = u.source AND d.version = u.version
WHERE lower(u.version) NOT LIKE lower('%ubuntu%')
AND lower(d.signed_by) LIKE lower('%Marco Trevisan%')
ORDER BY u.date DESC
</pre>

Computed via:
<pre>
SELECT source, version, date, changed_by, changed_by_name,
       changed_by_email, signed_by, signed_by_name, signed_by_email,
       distribution,
       array_to_string(ARRAY(
         SELECT bug
         FROM ubuntu_upload_history_launchpad_closes
         WHERE source = ubuntu_upload_history.source
           AND version = ubuntu_upload_history.version
       ), ' ') AS fixed
FROM ubuntu_upload_history
WHERE lower(signed_by) NOT LIKE lower('%Marco Trevisan%')
AND lower(changed_by) LIKE lower('%Marco Trevisan%')
ORDER BY date DESC
</pre>

See also: https://udd.debian.org/sponsorstats.cgi and https://piuparts.debian.org/sid/maintainer/m/marco@ubuntu.com.html for debian uploads.
